## Components

A React **component** is a JavaScript function whose name starts with a capital letter and which returns **JSX**. Components let you split the UI into independent, reusable pieces.

```jsx
function Greeting({ name }) {
  return <h1>Hello, {name}!</h1>;
}
```

## JSX

JSX looks like HTML but is really syntactic sugar for `React.createElement` calls. A few rules:

- Return a single root element (or a `<>…</>` fragment).
- Use `className` instead of `class`, and camelCase event props (`onClick`).
- Embed JavaScript expressions inside `{ }`.

```jsx
function Card({ title, items }) {
  return (
    <article className="card">
      <h2>{title}</h2>
      <ul>
        {items.map((item) => (
          <li key={item.id}>{item.label}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </article>
  );
}
```

Note the `key` prop on list items — React uses it to track elements efficiently.
